Description: Limestone ostracon: on the recto fourteen lines of a text containing a list of priced objects given to pay for a bull delivered by Amenmose. On the verso one line of text records the total sum of the payment: 119 'deben' of copper.
Curator's comments: Text: . J. Černy and A.H. Gardiner, ‘Hieratic Ostraca’ (Oxford 1957), pl. 86.1. Bibliography: S. Birch, 'Inscriptions in the Hieratic and Demotic Character, from the Collections of the British Museum' (London, 1868), pl. XV; J. Černy and A.H. Gardiner, ‘Hieratic Ostraca’ (Oxford 1957), p. 23 and pl. LXXXVI, 2; J.J. Janssen, 'Commodity Prices from the Ramessid Period' (Leiden, 1975), p. 79; K. Kitchen, 'Ramesside Inscriptions' V (Oxford 1983), 589.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (136361) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/136361)
